To pay supervision fees as determined by the DOC.

DOC shall withhold 25% of all inmate monies to pay fines/costs/surcharges/restitution.  The balance due shall be a condition of extended supervision/parole.  If discharged with financial obligations owing, a civil judgment shall be entered and/or other collection procedures will be implemented.

1)   No contact whatsoever with victim or victim's family members.

2)   No contact with any child under the age of 18 without approval of DOC Agent.

3)   Attend & complete sex offender treatment/counseling as directed by DOC Agent.

4)   Not to obtain any employment or do any volunteer work involving teaching or instructing Tae Kwon Do or any other instructor based teaching jobs or activities.

5)   Attend any counseling/treatment as deemed necessary.

6)   Absolute sobriety.  No illegal drug or alcohol use/purchase/consumption/possession.

7)   Not to enter into any bars/taversn/liquor stores or any place where the main purpose is the sale of alcohol.

8)   No use/purchase/consumption/possession of any prescription medication without a valid doctor's prescription.  No possession of any drug paraphernalia.

9)   Pay court costs.

10) Pay supervision fees as directed.
